From c65d747b095e64609790afb6d09af0418495fd78 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alejandro Pena <adpena@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 11:17:06 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/7] Harden fix per adversarial review: V2 retirement,
 deadline sweep, lifecycle enum
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Findings 1, 2, 3, 6 from the adversarial review:

1. V2 retirement path (Finding 1): the V1 completion watcher in
   `agent::control` is gated behind `!Feature::MultiAgentV2`, so V2
   spawned subagents never reached `retire_finalized_agent`. Wired V2
   retirement directly into `Session::maybe_notify_parent_of_terminal_turn`
   so that terminal `Completed` / `Errored` turns retire the slot in V2 as
   they already did in V1. `retire_finalized_agent` is now `pub(crate)`.

2. Explicit shutdown on retirement (Finding 2): `retire_finalized_agent`
   previously relied on the last `Arc<CodexThread>` being dropped to
   close the submission channel and trigger #19753's MCP teardown.
   Send `Op::Shutdown` explicitly (when the agent isn't already in
   `Shutdown`) so `session::handlers::shutdown` runs deterministically.
   Channel-closed errors are warned and ignored — same tolerance as
   `shutdown_live_agent`.

3. Lifecycle enum (Finding 3): replaced `slot_active: bool` plus
   `last_status: Option<AgentStatus>` with explicit `SlotState` enum
   (`NotTracked` / `Active` / `Retired { last_status }`). This removes
   the ambiguous "slot_active=false" state that could mean either
   "root, never tracked" or "retired spawned thread". `cached_status`
   and slot decrement logic now read directly from the enum.

6. Deadline-bounded descendant sweep (Finding 6): replaced the
   hardcoded 16-pass cap in `shutdown_live_descendants` with a
   wall-clock deadline (30 s) plus a 64-sweep soft cap. Logs a warning
   when the deadline or cap is hit so root teardown surfaces residual
   live descendants instead of silently spinning.
