Subject: [PATCH 5/7] Address pass-2 adversarial review (high-severity)

- V2 retirement detached via tokio::spawn (Pass-2 Finding 1).
  retire_finalized_agent's state.send_op(Op::Shutdown).await ran
  synchronously from Session::send_event -> maybe_notify_parent_of_terminal_turn,
  which can deadlock on the bounded (512-cap) submission channel because
  the receiver IS the same session loop. Mirror the V1 watcher pattern:
  spawn a task that holds an Arc<AgentControl> clone and runs the
  retirement asynchronously.

- Hard deadline for descendant sweep (Pass-2 Finding 2). Previously the
  30s deadline was only checked between sweeps; each
  shutdown_live_agent.await could block indefinitely on its own
  send_op. Now each call is wrapped in tokio::time::timeout_at, both
  the descendant lookup and each shutdown attempt enforce the deadline,
  and a 50ms sleep_until between residual sweeps prevents hot-looping
  CPU.
