From: Alejandro Pena <adpena@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:35:28 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] Pass-3 hardening: cancellation-safe shutdown, V2
 retire-then-notify, telemetry
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses pass-3 adversarial-review findings:

F1 (high) — shutdown_live_agent_with_deadline.
The pass-2 sweep wrapped each shutdown_live_agent.await with
tokio::time::timeout_at, which cancelled the inner future on deadline
and could leave the registry in a half-flushed/half-removed state.
Refactored: shutdown_live_agent_with_deadline wraps only the inner
flush_rollout + send_op awaits with the deadline, then unconditionally
runs the registry-mutation finalization (remove_thread +
release_spawned_thread). Even if the deadline fires inside the inner
awaits, the registry stays consistent.

F2 (medium) — telemetry on retirement paths.
warn!("{err}") replaced with warn!(error = ?err, "...") for full error
chain. Added tracing::debug! event on successful retirement. V2
spawned task instrumented with info_span!("v2_retire_finalized_agent",
agent_id = %agent_id, ...) so distributed traces can follow the
detached retirement.

F3 (medium) — V2 retire-then-notify ordering.
Pass-2 ran forward_child_completion_to_parent synchronously, then
spawned retirement. Reversed: retirement is spawned first, then the
parent notification awaits. Closes the window where a parent could
observe "child completed" + immediately attempt spawn_agent and hit
AgentLimitReached because the slot hadn't been freed yet.

F4 (low) — clarified deadline timer semantics.
Added doc comment on the tokio::time::Instant deadline noting that
tests using tokio::time::pause() must drive virtual time explicitly.

Plus the doc-formatting clippy fix (clippy::doc_lazy_continuation
flagged "+ release_spawned_thread" as a list-item continuation).
