From 892abf120f4f500ca0b7fcec2dc8cc194f9a1bb0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alejandro Pena <adpena@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 15:44:19 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] Scope down: remove descendant-drain (pass-3 finding,
 regression in resume tests)

`cargo test --workspace` on the fresh clone with the pass-2 patch surfaced
two regressions that pass-2's targeted-tests-only verification missed:

- resume_agent_from_rollout_reopens_open_descendants_after_manager_shutdown
- resume_agent_from_rollout_uses_edge_data_when_descendant_metadata_source_is_stale

Root cause: the descendant-drain added to session::handlers::shutdown
(originally meant to address defect #3, "root shutdown doesn't drain
descendants") races destructively with
ThreadManager::shutdown_all_threads_bounded. The bulk shutdown queues each
thread's shutdown_and_wait in parallel; when the parent's drain calls
shutdown_live_agent on its descendants concurrently with the bulk loop's
own shutdown of those same threads, the rollout writer ends up in a state
that resume_agent_from_rollout cannot recover from (flush_rollout returns
ThreadNotFound on the descendant).

Tried three fixes:
1. Cancellation-safe shutdown_live_agent_with_deadline (kept the race).
2. Signal-only descendant drain (still triggered submit_failed in bulk).
3. Skip already-removed descendants (helped one test but root_shutdown
   test still failed on different timing).

Conclusion: the descendant-drain mechanism needs cooperation with
ThreadManager so the two paths agree on cleanup authority. That's a
larger refactor than this patch's scope. Scoped down to defect #1
(slot retention on Completed/Errored), which remains intact and
verified across V1 + V2.

Removed:
- AgentControl::shutdown_live_descendants
- AgentControl::shutdown_live_agent_with_deadline
- AgentControl::shutdown_live_agent_send_op (helper)
- run_send_op_with_optional_deadline (free helper)
- AgentControl::clear_spawned_registry_for_root_shutdown
- AgentRegistry::clear_for_root_shutdown
- root_shutdown_shuts_down_live_spawned_descendants test
- clear_for_root_shutdown_releases_all_spawned_slots test
- All descendant-drain code from session::handlers::shutdown

Verification on the patched branch:
- cargo fmt --all -- --check: clean
- cargo clippy --workspace --tests -- -D warnings: clean
- 7 targeted tests pass (retire_releases_slot_and_preserves_cached_status,
  spawn_agent_releases_slot_after_completion (V1+V2),
  v2_spawn_agent_releases_slot_after_completion,
  failed_spawn_releases_reserved_nickname,
  retire_after_release_does_not_double_decrement,
  retire_is_idempotent_for_repeated_calls,
  release_after_retire_does_not_double_decrement).
- Both formerly-failing resume tests now pass:
  resume_agent_from_rollout_reopens_open_descendants_after_manager_shutdown,
  resume_agent_from_rollout_uses_edge_data_when_descendant_metadata_source_is_stale.
